# Google Calendar integration (optional)
#
# Chrome-Extension OAuth client id used by chrome.identity.getAuthToken to read
# the user's primary calendar (calendar.readonly). The client id is public — it
# ships inside the manifest — so it is not a secret, but it is build-specific.
# Leave it empty to ship without the live integration: an un-provisioned build
# hides the calendar companion entirely (there is no sample/preview data). See
# GOOGLE_CALENDAR.md for how to mint this in Google Cloud.
VITE_GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=
